HEADWORD: live-bearer
<hw>live-bearer</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>Any fish of the family
<fam>Poeciliiidae</fam>, small usually brightly-colored viviparous
surface-feeding fishes of fresh or brackish warm waters, often used in
mosquito control.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> topminnow, poeciliid fish, poeciliid.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lived</ent>⟦br⟧
